Volkswagen to Invest 3.4 Billion Euros in Brazil, DPA Reports

-- B y   A n d r e a s   C r e m e r
-- 
2011-10-04T06:01:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/volkswagen-to-invest-3-4-billion-euros-in-brazil-dpa-reports.html
Volkswagen AG (VOW)  plans to invest 3.4
billion euros ($4.5 billion) in Brazil through 2016,  Deutsche
Presse-Agentur  reported, citing Chief Executive Officer  Martin
Winterkorn .  Europe’s largest automaker last month said it planned to
spend a record 62.4 billion euros globally over the next five
years on factories, vehicles and research and development on
Volkswagen’s nine brands.  The company’s Chinese joint ventures, which aren’t
consolidated, will invest another 14 billion euros through 2016.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andreas Cremer in Berlin at 
 acremer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
